(2, 'happy mother day', '5246934771677962716.jpg', '2023-05-14', 'C:\\wamp64\\tmp\\php82B9.tmp', '<h2><strong>When is Mother&rsquo;s Day?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Mother&rsquo;s Day is the annual day for you to show your mum just how much she means to you. We know you appreciate her 365 days a year, but Mother&rsquo;s Day is about going the extra mile and treating your mother to a memorable day. This year, it takes place on&nbsp;<strong>Sunday 19th March</strong>, so make sure you&rsquo;re fully prepared to give your mum the best day possible! Don&rsquo;t worry if you&rsquo;re struggling to find the perfect gift, we&rsquo;ve got loads of ideas and deals, so you can make this year the best Mother&rsquo;s Day yet.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Who invented Mother&rsquo;s Day?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Ever wondered how this worldwide tradition began? Well, it started over 100 years ago, way back in 1908. Peace activist Anna Jarvis held a memorial to remember her mother, who treated wounded soldiers on both sides of the American Civil War. Anna Jarvis wanted to remember her, and all mothers every year, as she believed your mother is&nbsp;<strong>&ldquo;the person who has done more for you than anyone in the world&rdquo;</strong>. Here at BravoVoucher, we think the same, and we&rsquo;ve got loads of offers on&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bravovoucher.co.uk/category-gifts-jewellery-flowers.html\">flowers, jewellery</a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.bravovoucher.co.uk/category-health-beauty.html\">health &amp; beauty</a>, and more, to help you give your mother the day she deserves.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Why is Mother&#39;s&nbsp;Day different in the UK?</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Mother&rsquo;s Day, or Mothering Sunday, has a unique story in the UK. In the UK, the date on which Mothering Sunday is celebrated changes every year so that it can land on a Sunday. This is because Mothering Sunday first began as a church tradition and takes place three weeks before Easter on the fourth Sunday o